sequenceDiagram
    participant Browser as User Browser
    participant Gateway as TLS Gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant KAP as kube-auth-proxy<br/>4180/TCP HTTP
    participant OIDC as External OIDC Provider<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant OSOAUTH as OpenShift OAuth Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant OSAPI as OpenShift User API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Redis as Redis (optional)<br/>6379/TCP
    participant Upstream as Upstream Application<br/>HTTP plaintext

    Note over Browser,Upstream: Flow 1: OIDC Authentication (Browser)

    Browser->>Gateway: GET /oauth2/start<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    Gateway->>KAP: Forward (internal)<br/>HTTP/4180
    KAP->>Browser: 302 Redirect to OIDC Provider
    Browser->>OIDC: GET /authorize<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.2+<br/>Client ID
    OIDC->>Browser: Login Page
    Browser->>OIDC: POST credentials<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    OIDC->>Browser: 302 Redirect with Auth Code
    Browser->>Gateway: GET /oauth2/callback?code=...<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    Gateway->>KAP: Forward (internal)<br/>HTTP/4180
    KAP->>OIDC: POST /token<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.2+<br/>Client ID + Secret + Code
    OIDC-->>KAP: ID Token + Access Token
    KAP->>Redis: Store Session (optional)<br/>Redis/6379
    KAP-->>Browser: Set-Cookie + 302 Redirect
    Browser->>Gateway: GET /app<br/>Cookie Session
    Gateway->>KAP: Forward<br/>HTTP/4180
    KAP->>Upstream: Proxied Request<br/>HTTP plaintext<br/>Authenticated Headers
    Upstream-->>KAP: Response
    KAP-->>Browser: Response

    Note over Browser,Upstream: Flow 2: OpenShift OAuth Authentication (Browser)

    Browser->>Gateway: GET /oauth2/start<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    Gateway->>KAP: Forward<br/>HTTP/4180
    KAP->>OSOAUTH: GET /.well-known/oauth-authorization-server<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    OSOAUTH-->>KAP: OAuth Metadata
    KAP->>Browser: 302 Redirect to OpenShift OAuth
    Browser->>OSOAUTH: Login + Authorize<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    OSOAUTH->>Browser: 302 Redirect with Auth Code
    Browser->>Gateway: GET /oauth2/callback?code=...<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    Gateway->>KAP: Forward<br/>HTTP/4180
    KAP->>OSOAUTH: POST /token<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.2+<br/>Client Credentials + Code
    OSOAUTH-->>KAP: Access Token
    KAP->>OSAPI: GET /apis/user.openshift.io/v1/users/~<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.2+<br/>Bearer Token
    OSAPI-->>KAP: User Info
    KAP->>Upstream: Proxied Request<br/>HTTP plaintext<br/>Authenticated Headers
    Upstream-->>KAP: Response
    KAP-->>Browser: Response

    Note over Browser,Upstream: Flow 3: K8s ServiceAccount Token Validation

    participant K8sClient as K8s Client
    K8sClient->>Gateway: Request<br/>Bearer Token (SA Token)
    Gateway->>KAP: Forward<br/>HTTP/4180
    KAP->>K8sAPI: POST TokenReview<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.2+<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>KAP: TokenReview Result
    KAP->>Upstream: Proxied Request<br/>HTTP plaintext<br/>Authenticated Headers
    Upstream-->>KAP: Response
    KAP-->>K8sClient: Response

    Note over Browser,Upstream: Flow 4: kube-rbac-proxy Authorization

    participant KRBAC as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    K8sClient->>KRBAC: Request<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.2+<br/>Bearer Token (SA)
    KRBAC->>K8sAPI: POST SubjectAccessReview<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.2+<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>KRBAC: Authorization Result
    KRBAC->>Upstream: Proxied Request<br/>HTTP plaintext
    Upstream-->>KRBAC: Response
    KRBAC-->>K8sClient: Response
